Joseph "Keysie" Keyes (born 17 September 1995) is an Ireland international rugby league footballer who plays as a scrum-half and stand-off for the Halifax Panthers in the RFL Championship

He has previously played for the London Broncos in the Super League and Championship, and spent time on loan from the Broncos at the London Skolars in League 1. Keyes also played for the Bradford Bulls in League 1 and the Betfred Championship.
He spent 2021 in Super League for Hull KR
